data.enText: a formal agreement between two organizations, countries, etc.

data.chText: 在刚过去的七月，双方签订了和平条约。
data.enText: The two sides signed a peace accord last July.
in accord (with sth/sb)
in agreement with

data.chText: 这一行动不会符合我们的方针。
data.enText: This action would not be in accord with our policy.
of your own accord
without being asked, forced or helped
He came back of his own accord.
The symptoms will clear up of their own accord.
with one accord
if people do sth with one accord , they do it at the same time, because they agree with each other

data.chText: 给予，赠予，授予（权力、地位、某种待遇）
data.enText: to give sb/sth authority, status or a particular type of treatment

data.chText: 我们的社会赋予家庭以十分重要的地位。

data.hoverText: 动词+名词短语+名词短语

data.enText: Our society accords great importance to the family.

data.chText: 我们的社会赋予家庭以十分重要的地位。
data.enText: Our society accords the family great importance.
to agree with or match sth

data.chText: 这些结果和我们的预测相当一致。
data.enText: These results accord closely with our predictions.

simple_means.memory_skill: ac 加强 + cord 心，心脏 → 心贴心 → 一致

means: 授予(权力、地位、某种待遇)

ex.chText: 董事会最终就两个重要问题达成了一致。
ex.enText: The board finally reached agreement on two important issues.

ex.chText: 然而，并非所有学者都与他意见一致。
ex.enText: However, not all scholars were in agreement with him.

synonyms.bx: 指双方或有关各方意见的相同。

ex.chText: 这些结果似乎与先前的研究一致。
ex.enText: These results seem to be in accord with earlier research.

ex.chText: 该项目完全符合政府政策。
ex.enText: This project is completely in accord with government policy.

synonyms.bx: 通常用于 be in accord with sth 结构中，指观点、行为、结果等与某事物一致或相符合。

ex.chText: 牛津大学授予他博士头衔。
ex.enText: Oxford University conferred the title of doctor on him.

ex.chText: 总统授予她一枚奖章。
ex.enText: The President conferred a metal on her.

synonyms.bx: 尤指作为对所取得成绩的奖励而授予某人学位、荣誉、权利、名号等，常与介词 on/upon 连用。

ex.chText: 他被允许觐见国王。
ex.enText: He was accorded permission to meet the king.

ex.chText: 她受到冷遇。
ex.enText: She was accorded a cold welcome.

ex.chText: 我们的社会赋予家庭十分重要的地位。
ex.enText: Our society accords great importance to the family.

synonyms.bx: 指授予某人或某事物权力、地位、某种待遇等。

ex.chText: 她获得最优学生奖。
ex.enText: She was awarded for being the best student.

ex.chText: 她获得了去哈佛大学读书的奖学金。
ex.enText: She has been awarded a scholarship to study at Harvard.

ex.chText: 评委会授予他一等奖。
ex.enText: The panel of judges awarded him first prize.

synonyms.bx: 指官方或经正式研究决定后对成绩突出者或竞赛优胜者给予奖励、奖金等。

ex.chText: 奖品授给了优胜者。
ex.enText: The trophy is bestowed on the winner.

ex.chText: 该国给这位民族英雄颁发了国家最高奖章。
ex.enText: The country bestowed its highest medal upon the national hero.

synonyms.bx: 指授予某人具有重大价值或意义的东西，尤用于表示尊重，常和介词 on/upon 连用。

ex.chText: 这份副本与原件不符。
ex.enText: This copy does not correspond with the original.

ex.chText: 这些标记与地图上的各点相对应。
ex.enText: The marks correspond to points on the map.

ex.chText: 他对事件的陈述与她说的不符。
ex.enText: His accounts of events do not correspond with hers.

synonyms.bx: 指两个事物或观点在某一方面或内容上互相匹配一致，常后接介词  with/to。

ex.chText: 她那漂亮的言辞与肮脏的行为不相符合。
ex.enText: Her beautiful words and dirty actions do not accord.

ex.chText: 你的行为与你的原则不符。
ex.enText: Your behaviour does not accord with your principle.

synonyms.bx: 常指行为、观点、性格、质量等方面一致，常后接介词 with。

ex.chText: 几个证人的陈述并不一致。
ex.enText: The witnesses' statements don't agree with each other.

ex.chText: 他的叙述和警方说的不一致。
ex.enText: His story doesn't agree with what the police have said.

synonyms.bx: 普通用词，指两条信息等相符或一致，常后接介词 with。

ex.chText: 我们的意见不统一。
ex.enText: We didn't coincide in opinion.

ex.chText: 我的宗教信仰跟你的不同。
ex.enText: My religious beliefs don't coincide with yours.

synonyms.bx: 多指想法、观点等一致或相符，常后接介词 with。

ex.chText: 我们对安排方面的意见与董事会一致。
ex.enText: Our opinions on the arrangement concur with those of the board.

ex.chText: 关于出口问题，我同意你的看法。
ex.enText: I concur with your opinion on exports.

synonyms.bx: 强调意见一致，一般用于正式场合，常后接介词 with。

ex.chText: 他的行为与社会习俗相左。
ex.enText: His behaviour doesn't conform to the customs of society.

ex.chText: 你遵守交通规则吗？
ex.enText: Do you conform to the traffic rules?

synonyms.bx: 强调一致性，也指遵照已确立的规则或模式行事，常后接介词 to。

ex.chText: 通商/友好/双边互助条约
ex.enText: the treaty of commerce/friendship/mutual assistance

ex.chText: 该条约是在平等的基础上订立的。
ex.enText: The treaty was concluded on equal terms.

ex.chText: 该条约将成为持久和平的开端。
ex.enText: The treaty will be the threshold of lasting peace.

ex.chText: 战争结束后，两国起草了一份和平协议。
ex.enText: The two nations drew up a peace treaty after the war ended.

synonyms.bx: 指国家之间经外交谈判后依照国际法签订的正式条约。

ex.chText: 赫尔辛基人权协议
ex.enText: the Helsinki accord on human rights

ex.chText: 这两个超级大国达成了一项协议。
ex.enText: The two superpowers reached an accord.

ex.chText: 那些国家共同签订了和平协定。
ex.enText: Those nations signed the peace accord.

synonyms.bx: 多指国家或团体之间达成的正式协议。

ex.chText: 他已签约去一家私企工作。
ex.enText: He was under contract to a private company.

ex.chText: 他们真的会签署那份合约吗？
ex.enText: Is it true that they will sign the contract?

ex.chText: 合同上的条款是完全公平的。
ex.enText: The terms of the contract are absolutely fair.

synonyms.bx: 指双方或多方订立的具有法律效力的正式书面合同或契约。

ex.chText: 这两个部落签署了一项终止战争的协定。
ex.enText: The two tribes signed a pact to end their fighting.

ex.chText: 早期移民和当地人缔结了和平条约。
ex.enText: The early immigrants concluded a peace pact with the local people.

ex.chText: 这使得两国签订了一项互不侵犯条约。
ex.enText: This led to a non-aggression pact between the two countries.

synonyms.bx: 尤指互助、停战等方面的正式协定。

in agreement with

data.chText: 这一行动不会符合我们的方针。
data.enText: This action would not be in accord with our policy.
of your own accord

He came back of his own accord.
The symptoms will clear up of their own accord.
with one accord
if people do sth with one accord , they do it at the same time, because they agree with each other

tr: a written agreement between two states or sovereigns

example: we are in accord with your proposal

tr: harmony of people's opinions or actions or characters
example: the two parties were in agreement

value.def: An accord between countries or groups of people is a formal agreement, for example to end a war.

example.ex: ...a fitting way to celebrate the peace accord.
example.tran: 庆祝和平协定的恰当的方式

gramarinfo.label: usu with supp, oft n N

value.tran: （国家、团体之间的正式）协定，协议，条约

value.def: If you are accorded a particular kind of treatment, people act towards you or treat you in that way.

example.ex: His predecessor was accorded an equally tumultuous welcome...
example.tran: 他的前任受到了同样热烈的欢迎。

example.ex: The government accorded him the rank of Colonel...
The treatment accorded to a United Nations official was little short of insulting.
example.tran: 联合国官员所受到的这种待遇几近羞辱。

value.def: If one fact, idea, or condition accords with another, they are in agreement and there is no conflict between them.

example.ex: Such an approach accords with the principles of socialist ideology.
example.tran: 这种方法与社会主义意识形态的原则相符。

example.ex: ...scientific evidence that did not fully accord with the facts uncovered by the police.
example.tran: 与警方所掌握的情况不完全一致的科学证据

value.def: If one person, action, or fact is in accord with another, they are in agreement and there is no conflict between them. You can also say that two people or things are in accord.

example.ex: ...this military action, taken in accord with United Nations resolutions...
example.tran: 依据联合国决议而采取的本次军事行动

example.ex: Old enemies can become new friends even if all their national interests are not in complete accord.
example.tran: 即使国家利益不尽相同，他们也可以化敌为友。

gramarinfo.label: v-link PHR, PHR after v, oft PHR <l>with</l> n

value.def: If something happens of its own accord, it seems to happen by itself, without anyone making it happen.

example.ex: In many cases the disease will clear up of its own accord.
example.tran: 这种病很多情况下会自愈。

value.def: If you do something of your own accord, you do it because you want to, without being asked or forced.

example.ex: He did not quit as France's prime minister of his own accord.
example.tran: 他辞去法国总理职务并非出于自愿。

value.def: If a number of people do something with one accord, they do it together or at the same time, because they agree about what should be done.

example.ex: With one accord they turned and walked back over the grass.
example.tran: 他们步调一致地转身走过草坪。
